<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3764] LeaderChangeStateCleanupTest.testStateCleanupAfterListenerNotification fails on Travis</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3764</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;LeaderChangeStateCleanupTest.testStateCleanupAfterListenerNotification&lt;/tt&gt; fails spuriously on Travis because of a &lt;tt&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/tt&gt;. The reason is that it&apos;s not properly waited until the &lt;tt&gt;ResourceManager&lt;/tt&gt; has been started. Due to this, it can happen that a leader notification message is tried to be sent to a &lt;tt&gt;LeaderRetrievalListener&lt;/tt&gt; which has not been set by the &lt;tt&gt;ResourceManager&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://s3.amazonaws.com/archive.travis-ci.org/jobs/123271732/log.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://s3.amazonaws.com/archive.travis-ci.org/jobs/123271732/log.txt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12959129">FLINK-3764</key>
